name: The Queen's Dreams: Swan Lake
description:
Too many years had she roamed unsure. Feeling out of place yet stuck.
The feathers pricked out of all the awkward parts causing her to itch and writhe.
She felt no option but to sleep.
She slept for what seemed like days.
And one day as she slumbered, the drips of her enclosure began to sound further apart.
Something told her the hibernation was over.
And so she crept out from her dark space.
Slowly and slower still.
A bright florescent hue filled the entrance.
An aura so bright it could be seen for miles.
But it was no aura.
It was her.
